    <h2 class="case-section__title">About</h2>
    <p>Peddie School is one of the nation's leading independent college-preparatory boarding schools. I managed the production of all multimedia in support of the school's brand, serving as staff photographer and videographer while directing external vendors for signature deliverables.</p>
  </section>
  <section class="case-section" data-animate>
    <p class="case-section__label">// what i did</p>
    <h2 class="case-section__title">What I Did</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Strategized, directed, shot, and edited films that told the Peddie story in a compelling, consistent visual format across all mediums</li>
      <li>Designed graphics for social media and advertising</li>
      <li>Managed social media for school accounts</li>
      <li>Managed vendor relationships for high-level production deliverables</li>
      <li>Co-led the redesign of peddie.org in partnership with Electric Kite</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section class="case-section" data-animate>
    <p class="case-section__label">// why it mattered</p>
    <h2 class="case-section__title">Why It Mattered</h2>
    <p>This role was a bridge between education and full-time institutional communications — the place where my classroom instincts and my production skills converged into a focused professional identity. It sharpened my ability to think strategically about brand, audience, and story at the institutional level.</p>
